{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_23","type":"agent_message","text":"The current behavior is internally inconsistent: `checkMetadataFiles` treats this exact coordinate as “nothing to do,” while `run-consecutive-tests` later treats the same coordinate as an error. That usually means the matrix builder is allowed to emit entries that do not correspond to a strict, runnable metadata/test directory pair. I’m tracing that selection logic now instead of patching the shell script blindly."}}
